uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.table

Class TableTransitionProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.table.TableTransitionProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, IndexTransitionFactory<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, IndexTransitionProvider<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, TransitionFactory<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, TransitionProvider<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, ViewTransitionFactory<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, ViewTransitionProvider<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>

    public class TableTransitionProvider
extends java.lang.Object
implements ViewTransitionProvider<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, IndexTransitionProvider<TableTransitionKey,TableTransitionTarget>, Contexed
    Class implementing transitions on factory classes identified by table. The target factory has implement TableTransitionTarget and have its class registered as a configuration property. This TransitionProvider needs to be registered under the name Table to enable this feature.
    Author:
    spb

      • getTransitions

        public java.util.Set<TableTransitionKey> getTransitions(TableTransitionTarget target)
        Description copied from interface: TransitionFactory
        Get a list of all the transition keys supported by the target type to be presented to the user as a set of possible options in a view transition. Options in this list that are not allowed by TransitionFactory.allowTransition(AppContext, Object, Object) will not be presented. Additional hidden operations may also be supported but these will never be presented to the user as options and can only generated as a ChainedTransitionResult.
